James F. Brooks from PolWatchers reviews the final debate in Poland’s Presidential Election between Komorowski and Lepper with partial results suggesting that this time both major candidates will win a majority in the final round The debate was postponed by a day to bring the debate forward to a time where the vote had been in progress for one hour rather than the original two hours that the debate was scheduled for We provide the video above without commentary and will allow our readers to judge their own assessment of the candidates (Likely Parliamentary Turnout) – male 2.74, women 2.44
